 Hodgson","126560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837442","Home Office","false","2018-02-21","<p>The Home Office invited the Local Authority Prevent Coordinator network, along with members of their communities, to attend the launch of the Making a Stand campaign, which the Home Secretary attended.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2018-02-21T11:14:30.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837442/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837442/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837442/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-05","Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department provided letters on behalf of the Making a Stand campaign led by INSPIRE (a) nationally and (b) through local prevent officers; and if she will publish correspondence, including electronic communication, between her Department and INSPIRE on that campaign.","false","Biography information for Naz Shah","Bradford West","Naz Shah","126561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837443","Home Office","false","2018-02-08","<p>Through the Research Information and Communications Unit, the Home Office works in partnership with a range of civil society organisations to counter a range of public safety issues, including counter-terrorism, counter-extremism, and serious and organised crime.</p><p>We provide access to communications professionals and industry experts, including Breakthrough Media.</p><p>This support was provided to Inspire in 2014 for the Making a Stand campaign which encouraged communities to publically state their rejection of Daesh and their abhorrence of extremism and terrorism.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2018-02-08T11:28:59.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837443/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837443/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837443/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-05","Radicalism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, to publish the correspondence between the Research Information and Communications Unit of her Department and (a) Breakthrough Media (b) Sara Khan and (c) Inspire between 2011 and 2017.","false","Biography information for Naz Shah","Bradford West","Naz Shah","126562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837444","Department for Education","false","2018-02-12","<p>The department receives correspondence from parents, including complaints. To differentiate complaints from other correspondence relating to special educational needs and disability would require a significant update to our correspondence management system.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","126322","2018-02-12T17:27:37.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837444/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837444/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837444/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-05","Special Educational Needs: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many complaints he or his predecessors have received in relation to local authorities acting on (a) Education, Health and Care Plans and (b) the Local Offer under the provisions of sections 496 and 497 of the Education Act 1996.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","126563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837445","Department for Education","false","2018-02-13","<p>ESOL (English for Speakers of Other Languages) Plus Mandation refers to specified funding that was discontinued in 2015 by the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills. The department’s data showed that the numbers being referred to provision were significantly lower than originally envisaged.</p><p> </p><p>The government continues to provide full funding for unemployed job seekers to improve their English, through a provider’s Adult Education Budget. Other learners are eligible for 50 per cent funding of course costs. In the academic year 2016-17, the government supported 114,100 ESOL learners using funds from the Adult Education Budget. Providers have the freedom and flexibility to deliver ESOL provision to best meet local needs.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-02-13T13:00:35.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837445/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837445/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837445/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-05","English Language: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much funding the Skills Funding Agency has provided for ESOL Plus Mandation courses since 2016; and how much such funding is forecast to be spent in 2018.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","126564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837446","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-02-12","<p>The table below details the budget for the Employment Agency Standard’s (EAS) Inspectorate and the number of staff employed by EAS since 2016:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Employment Agency Standard Inspectorate Budget</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of Full Time Equivalent Staff for each year</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>£500,000</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>£500,000</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>£725,000*</p></td><td><p>12</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>*The increase in budget was provided to purchase new IT systems to increase casework productivity and support EAS’ intelligence capability.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Full information regarding the activity of the Employment Agency Standards Inspectorate can be found in in their annual reports. These can be found at the following location:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-agency-standards-eas-inspectorate-annual-reports" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-agency-standards-eas-inspectorate-annual-reports</a></p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths","126332","2018-02-12T17:34:55.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837446/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837446/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/837446/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-05","Employment Agency Standards Inspectorate","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how much funding has been allocated from the public purse to the Employment Agency Standards Inspectorate since 2016; and how many FTE